race.comment: MIRAI SAN (2) two runs back have been okay and he looks to get the right setup for this with Drew's 2kg claim. Covered plenty of ground throughout from the wide draw when a tidy sixth over 1250m at Taree. Rates highly and no excuse against this lot. BLUE DE BEERS (4) improving colt who can go on with it this time in. Slick first-up winner at Bathurst, then faded late over the 1200m at Gilgandra when fourth. Set to peak in this weaker contest and the cross-over nose band comes off. IT'S A TATA (5) got off the mark at his second run back with a dominant victory over 1100m at Gilgandra from the outside barrier. Has further scope for improvement from the right draw. Each-way. THE NEPHILIM (7) shouldered the 59kg when he returned from a let-up with a fading sixth over 1100m at Armidale. Massive weight drop for this and shapes as a value contender.
